<div id="android-mdm" v-cloak>
  <div purpose="landing-page-container">
    <div purpose="landing-page-content">
      <div purpose="landing-page-hero">
        <div purpose="hero-row">
          <div purpose="page-hero-content">
            <div purpose="page-hero-headings">
              <h4>Android Device Management</h4>
              <h1>Open source Android MDM for modern IT and security teams</h1>
            </div>
            <div purpose="page-hero-text">
              <p>Enroll, configure, and secure Android phones and tablets at enterprise scale. Manage Android alongside macOS, iOS, iPadOS, Windows, Linux, and ChromeOS in one place.</p>
            </div>
            <div purpose="button-row">
              <a purpose="cta-button" class="btn btn-primary" href="/contact">Get a demo</a>
              <animated-arrow-button href="/gitops-workshop">Join a workshop</animated-arrow-button>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div purpose="hero-logos">
          <logo-carousel></logo-carousel>
        </div>
      </div><%/* landing-page-hero */%>

      <div purpose="landing-page-section">
        <div purpose="section-heading">
          <h3>Traditional Android MDM is holding IT back</h3>
          <p>Most Android management tools bolt onto a closed-source console with limited support for modern Android Enterprise, weak BYOD privacy, and no real cross-platform story.</p>
        </div>
        <div purpose="four-column-feature-row">
          <div purpose="feature-item">
            <h5>Vendor lock-in</h5>
            <p>Proprietary tools trap configurations behind GUIs, with steep renewals and limited export.</p>
          </div>
          <div purpose="feature-item">
            <h5>Manual ClickOps</h5>
            <p>Profile and policy changes happen in a console with no version history or peer review.</p>
          </div>
          <div purpose="feature-item">
            <h5>Android afterthought</h5>
            <p>Tools designed around Windows or Mac treat Android as a checkbox, not a first-class platform.</p>
          </div>
          <div purpose="feature-item">
            <h5>BYOD privacy concerns</h5>
            <p>Legacy agents reach into personal data on employee-owned phones, eroding trust and adoption.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div purpose="landing-page-section">
        <div purpose="feature-with-image">
          <div purpose="feature-image">
            <img alt="A screenshot of Fleet managing Android devices." src="/images/fleet-mdm-hero-1006x595@2x.png">
          </div>
          <div purpose="feature-text">
            <h3>Manage Android with the visibility and control modern IT teams need</h3>
            <p>Fleet is open source Android device management built on Google's Android Management API and Android Enterprise. Enroll, configure, and secure every Android host in your fleet without giving up transparency or cross-platform support.</p>
            <div purpose="checklist">
              <p>Connect Android Enterprise to Fleet with a free subscription through Google Workspace, Microsoft 365, or any work email.</p>
              <p>Enroll BYOD hosts with a Work Profile that keeps personal data separate from corporate apps.</p>
              <p>Push configuration profiles, managed app configurations, and certificates from version-controlled JSON.</p>
              <p>Deploy public and private Android apps from managed Google Play, including custom APKs.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div purpose="landing-page-section">
        <div purpose="section-heading">
          <h2>Built for Android Enterprise</h2>
          <p>Whether you manage a handful of field devices or tens of thousands of phones, Fleet gives Android admins the depth Google's platform deserves and the cross-platform reach the rest of the business needs.</p>
        </div>
        <div purpose="feature-row">
          <div purpose="feature-item">
            <h5>Android Enterprise integration</h5>
            <p>Connect Android Enterprise to Fleet in minutes. Free subscription, no extra cost from Google to manage your hosts.</p>
          </div>
          <div purpose="feature-item">
            <h5>BYOD Work Profile</h5>
            <p>Enroll personal Android devices with a Work Profile that segments corporate apps and data from the user's personal information.</p>
          </div>
          <div purpose="feature-item">
            <h5>QR code and link enrollment</h5>
            <p>Send end users a Fleet enrollment link or QR code. The Work Profile sets up in a few taps.</p>
          </div>
          <div purpose="feature-item">
            <h5>Configuration profiles</h5>
            <p>Apply policies and settings using JSON configuration profiles, from password complexity to network configuration.</p>
          </div>
          <div purpose="feature-item">
            <h5>Managed Google Play apps</h5>
            <p>Add public apps from Google Play and deploy them to teams or self-service. Apps install silently in the Work Profile.</p>
          </div>
          <div purpose="feature-item">
            <h5>Custom Android apps (APK)</h5>
            <p>Publish private APKs through managed Google Play and deliver them to your hosts. Updates flow the same way.</p>
          </div>
          <div purpose="feature-item">
            <h5>Managed app configurations</h5>
            <p>Configure app behavior centrally with managed app configurations, so apps land pre-configured for your environment.</p>
          </div>
          <div purpose="feature-item">
            <h5>Enterprise Wi-Fi with EAP-TLS</h5>
            <p>Deploy SCEP certificates and 802.1X EAP-TLS Wi-Fi configurations to fully-managed and Work Profile hosts.</p>
          </div>
          <div purpose="feature-item">
            <h5>BYOD migration from another MDM</h5>
            <p>Send users a single enrollment link to remove the old Work Profile and join Fleet, no manual rebuild needed.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div purpose="landing-page-section">
        <div purpose="feature-with-image">
          <div purpose="feature-text">
            <h3>GitOps and AI-ready Android device management</h3>
            <p>Every Fleet configuration is a file. Store your Android profiles, policies, app configurations, and software in your own Git repository. Review device changes the way you review code, ship them through CI, and roll back with a single revert.</p>
            <div purpose="checklist">
              <p>Version-controlled Android configuration profiles, managed app configurations, and policies in YAML and JSON.</p>
              <p>Peer-review device changes in pull requests before they reach production.</p>
              <p>Generate Fleet config with any LLM, from ChatGPT and Claude to private models.</p>
              <p>Audit history, rollback, and CI/CD for your entire Android estate.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div purpose="feature-image">
            <img alt="A screenshot of Fleet running reports across managed devices." src="/images/linux-management-feature-image-scripts-504x378@2x.png">
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div purpose="landing-page-section">
        <div purpose="section-heading">
          <h2>Self-hosted, Fleet-hosted, or air-gapped</h2>
          <p>Run Fleet wherever your security and compliance teams need it, with the same features either way. Your device data stays inside your network.</p>
        </div>
        <div purpose="feature-row">
          <div purpose="feature-item">
            <h5>Open source core</h5>
            <p>Fleet is MIT-licensed open source. Read the code, audit how Android hosts are managed, and adapt it to your needs.</p>
          </div>
          <div purpose="feature-item">
            <h5>Run it where you want</h5>
            <p>Deploy Fleet on AWS, Azure, GCP, your own data center, or use Fleet Cloud with 100% feature parity.</p>
          </div>
          <div purpose="feature-item">
            <h5>One console, every platform</h5>
            <p>See Android, macOS, iOS, iPadOS, Windows, Linux, and ChromeOS in one inventory and one policy engine.</p>
          </div>
          <div purpose="feature-item">
            <h5>API-first by design</h5>
            <p>Every feature in the Fleet UI is available over the REST API. Integrate with Okta, Jira, Slack, Snowflake, and your SIEM.</p>
          </div>
          <div purpose="feature-item">
            <h5>Play Protect certified hosts</h5>
            <p>Fleet supports Android devices that are Play Protect certified, including Google Pixel and Samsung Galaxy.</p>
          </div>
          <div purpose="feature-item">
            <h5>Built in the open</h5>
            <p>Fleet's roadmap, code, and conversations are public. File an issue, send a PR, or ship a feature with us.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

    </div>
  </div>
  <div purpose="tweets-container" class="container-fluid px-md-0 pb-0 d-flex flex-column justify-content-center">
    <div purpose="section-heading" class="mx-auto text-center">
      <h2 class="mb-3">What IT and security teams are saying</h2>
    </div>
  </div>
  <scrollable-tweets :testimonials="testimonialsForScrollableTweets"></scrollable-tweets>
  <div purpose="bottom-gradient">

    <div purpose="page-container" class="container">
      <div purpose="bottom-cta" class="text-center">
        <h4>Android Device Management</h4>
        <h2>Modern, open source MDM for every Android device</h2>
        <div purpose="button-row" style="margin-top: 32px;" class="d-flex justify-content-center align-items-center mx-auto">
          <a purpose="cta-button" class="btn btn-primary" href="/contact">Get a demo</a>
          <animated-arrow-button href="/gitops-workshop">Join a workshop</animated-arrow-button>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
  <%/* Cloud city banner */%>
  <parallax-city></parallax-city>
  <modal purpose="video-modal" v-if="modal === 'fleet-in-three-minutes'" @close="closeModal()">
    <iframe width="560" height="315" src="https://www.youtube-nocookie.com/embed/q1Tm3IBcx24?rel=0&autoplay=1" title="YouTube video player" frameborder="0" allow="accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share" allowfullscreen></iframe>
  </modal>
</div>
<%- /* Expose server-rendered data as window.SAILS_LOCALS :: */ exposeLocalsToBrowser() %>
